Currently backing up twenty years of music onto hard drives and placing them near the studio door in case the wildfire on the adjacent mountain decides to come our way.

A human caused wildfire. 

It breaks my heart to see the gorgeous forests I’ve hiked in since I was a teen go up in smoke and because of our negligence. It’s equally terrifying to go through your belonging and decide what’s worth the risk of taking. My husband lost everything in a fire in 2017. We should all chip in to help any and everyone that is being blindsided by these preventable catastrophes. 

If I created a fundraiser for wildfires in Canada with a song, who would help spread the word?!
Tonight’s the night! Make sure you watch our new little movie @hallmarkmovie #Somethingnew

I didn’t know
I’d only fall in love alone ✨

Rest in peace #sineadoconnor 💔 I was given the very special privilege of opening for her once. She is and will forever be, to me, a beautiful flame, a reminder to live by the rules of your own and very precious muse and by no others. Rest in peace beauty. You inspired so many of us young girls to become women, to do the art we love because we love it and for that reason alone, and I hope you find peace.

WHAT ARE YOU DOING NEW YEAR’S EVE

I’ve always adored this tune sung by #ellafitzgerald. And it’s always made me tear up. Maybe because there is so much to each new year. Maybe because of the losses and gains of each year as they pass. So lovely to sing along to  @jackramsey87 with this gorgeous microphone from @ribbonmics ♥️

Love you all. Happy New Years. Let’s make 2024 one to remember xoxo
